{{NCAATeamSeason |Mode=Basketball |Year=2008â09 |Prev year=2007â08 |Next year=2009â10 |Team=South Carolina Gamecocks |Image=Usc-gamecocks-text-logo.gif |ImageSize=100 |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division= East |ShortConference=SEC |CoachRank= |APRank= |Record=21â10 |ConfRecord=10â6 |HeadCoach=[[Darrin Horn]] |AsstCoach1=Michael Boynton |AsstCoach2=Cypheus Bunton |AsstCoach3=Scott Cherry |StadiumArena=[[Colonial Life Arena]] |Champion=SEC East Co-Champions |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{2008â09 Southeastern Conference men's basketball standings}} The '''2008â09 South Carolina men's basketball team''' represents [[University of South Carolina]]. The head coach is [[Darrin Horn]] who is in his first season with the Gamecocks. The team plays its home games in the 18,000-seat [[Colonial Life Arena]] in [[Columbia, SC|Columbia]], [[South Carolina]]. All games will be produced and [[Radio broadcasting|broadcasted locally]] by the Gamecock Sports Radio Network.
==Regular season== On November 14, 2008, Carolina defeated the Jacksonville State Gamecocks 89â76 to win the first game of the Darrin Horn Era at USC.
On December 2, 2008, Carolina defeated Princeton 84â58, handing the Tigers their worst defeat in Jadwin Gym since it opened in 1969.
On January 2, 2009, Carolina defeated #19 Baylor, 85â84.
On January 21, 2009, Carolina defeated #24 Florida, 70â69.
On January 31, 2009, Carolina defeated #24 Kentucky, 78â77, the Gamecocks' second win in history at Rupp Arena.
On February 25, 2009, Carolina defeated Kentucky 77â59, setting a school-record for blocked shots with 16, and sweeping the season series with the Wildcats for only the second time (1997) since joining the SEC.
